# Risk Engine Project Overview

This document outlines the target architecture, modular structure, and module descriptions for the Risk Engine. It is designed to act as a production-grade, highly-extensible framework for calculating and storing various financial risk metrics.

---

## 1. Directory Structure & Architecture

Below is the directory structure for the risk engine, showing how calculators, storage, testing, configuration, and CI/CD pipelines are organized.

```text
risk_engine/
├── calculators/
│   ├── base_calculator.py       ← abstract base class (framework)
│   ├── market_risk/
│   │   ├── var_calculator.py    ← Historical & Parametric VaR implementation
│   │   └── data_loader.py       ← yfinance data ingestion
│   ├── credit_risk/
│   │   └── pfe_calculator.py    ← Potential Future Exposure
│   └── liquidity/
│       └── lcr_calculator.py    ← Liquidity Coverage Ratio
├── storage/
│   ├── models.py                ← SQLAlchemy ORM models
│   └── repository.py            ← write/query risk results
├── tests/
│   ├── unit/
│   │   ├── test_var.py
│   │   ├── test_pfe.py
│   │   └── test_lcr.py
│   └── bdd/
│       ├── features/
│       │   ├── var.feature      ← Gherkin scenarios
│       │   ├── pfe.feature
│       │   └── lcr.feature
│       └── steps/
│           ├── var_steps.py
│           └── lcr_steps.py
├── config/
│   └── settings.py              ← DB URL, thresholds, run params
├── main.py                      ← CLI entry point
├── sonar-project.properties     ← SonarQube config
├── pyproject.toml
└── .github/workflows/ci.yml     ← pytest + coverage on push
```

